On 5th of March, the first case of COVID-19 appeared in the country of 59,212,004 people, it was a man who came back from Italy https://www.gov.za/speeches/health-reports-first-case-covid-19-coronavirus-5-mar-2020-0000. Table 9 contains the data of South Africa for thirteen weeks. That are 5th to 17th weeks of the pandemic in the area. Unlike northern hemisphere, in South Africa, the winter season starts in June. The corresponding rates for each week have been calculated and given in Table 9. The graphs for both the rates are given in Figs. 14 and 15.Table 9
